âœ… Correct Pure-FTPd Command (no username, no password)

Please stop old containers:

docker stop ftp-anon-only
docker rm ftp-anon-only


Now run this instead:

docker run -d `
  --name ftp-anon-only `
  -p 21:21 -p 20:20 -p 21100-21110:21100-21110 `
  -v C:\ftp\upload:/var/ftp:rw `
  stilliard/pure-ftpd:hardened `
  pure-ftpd -E -A -x -j -R -P 192.168.2.7 -p 21100:21110

What these flags mean:

-E â†’ only anonymous logins allowed

-A â†’ donâ€™t ask for password

-x â†’ disable downloads (upload-only)

-j â†’ chroot (stay inside folder)

-R â†’ disallow symlinks

-P â†’ public IP (192.168.2.7)

-p â†’ passive port range

